-- Heat Beat Knicks 104-94 to Lead NBA Playoff Series 2-0 in Games
-- B y   D e x   M c L u s k e y
-- 2012-05-01T01:39:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-01/heat-beat-knicks-104-94-to-lead-nba-playoff-series-2-0-in-games.html
The  Miami Heat  defeated the New
York Knicks 104-94 to lead their National Basketball Association
first-round playoff series by two games to none.  Dwyane Wade scored 25 points, Chris Bosh added 21 and
LeBron James contributed 19 for the Heat at AmericanAirlines
Arena in Miami. Carmelo Anthony had a game-high 30 points for
the Knicks.  The best-of-seven series resumes with Game 3 at Madison
Square Garden in New York on May 3.  The Knicks have now lost 12 straight playoffs games, tying
the Memphis Grizzlies for the most consecutive postseason
defeats in the NBA.  Also tonight, the Orlando Magic and Oklahoma City Thunder
seek to take 2-0 leads in their series, against the  Indiana
Pacers  and Dallas Mavericks respectively.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dex McLuskey at 
 dmcluskey@bloomberg.net  